lightning: lightning (generate machine code at runtime)
lightning:
lightning: GNU lightning is a C library for generating machine code at runtime.
lightning: It provides an API for building programs in an idealised RISC-like machine
lightning: language, and then converting the program to native machine code in memory.
lightning: The program is returned as a function pointer which can be called just like any
lightning: other function.
lightning:
lightning: Homepage: https://www.gnu.org/software/lightning/
